---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---
<Layout region="uk" title="FAQ – Alturascope UK">
  <section id="faq" class="py-16 lg:py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">
          FAQ &amp; How We Work With You
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base text-slate-600">
          A quick look at how Alturascope UK fits into your process, what we deliver, and the edges of
          our service. If you don’t see your question here, just reach out&mdash;we’re happy to talk
          through your specific sites.
        </p>
      </div>
      <!-- FAQ grid -->
      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        <!-- Q1 -->
        <article class="group rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20 overflow-hidden">
          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">
            Booking &amp; timing
          </h2>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">
            How far ahead do we need to book?
          </h3>
          <div class="mt-2 transition-all duration-200 ease-out max-h-0 opacity-0 group-hover:max-h-[2000px] group-hover:opacity-100">
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-700">
              For standard visits, we ask for <span class="font-medium">7&ndash;10 business days</span>
              from confirmed access to site. That gives us time to lock in travel, coordinate with
              building management, and align on your brief.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
              We can often accommodate tighter timelines on a
              <span class="font-medium">rush basis (+25%)</span>. Very last-minute, night
              (6pm&ndash;6am), or weekend work carries a <span class="font-medium">+50%</span> uplift
              and is subject to availability and site rules.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <!-- Q2 -->
        <article class="group rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20 overflow-hidden">
          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">
            Site size &amp; complexity
          </h2>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">
            What if the space is bigger than 10,000 sq ft?
          </h3>
          <div class="mt-2 transition-all duration-200 ease-out max-h-0 opacity-0 group-hover:max-h-[2000px] group-hover:opacity-100">
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-700">
              Our published pricing is based on <span class="font-medium">spaces up to 10,000 sq ft</span>
              with typical commercial complexity. Larger sites, multi-floor portfolios, or heavy plant /
              industrial areas are absolutely doable&mdash;they just need a bit more planning.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
              In those cases we’ll usually:
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-slate-700">
              <li>Break the work into sensible zones or floors.</li>
              <li>Adjust pricing based on total area and complexity.</li>
              <li>Confirm any additional time needed for capture and reporting.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-500">
              You’ll always see the adjusted scope and fee before we mobilise.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <!-- Q3 -->
        <article class="group rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20 overflow-hidden">
          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">
            Deliverables
          </h2>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">
            What exactly do you deliver after each visit?
          </h3>
          <div class="mt-2 transition-all duration-200 ease-out max-h-0 opacity-0 group-hover:max-h-[2000px] group-hover:opacity-100">
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-700">
              Every standard visit includes a consistent bundle of visuals and documentation so your
              team can make decisions quickly:
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-slate-700">
              <li>Digital twin or 360&deg; walkthrough of the space.</li>
              <li>Labeled photo storyboard covering shell, core, MEP, ceilings, floors, and issues.</li>
              <li>
                Fixture and services counts (lights, diffusers, sprinklers, washrooms, doors, key
                equipment, etc.).
              </li>
              <li>
                A detailed written conditions report with a high-level mechanical / services overview,
                upsides &amp; concerns clearly highlighted, and recommendations prioritised into
                P1 / P2 / P3.
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
              For progress visits you also receive a focused <span class="font-medium">exceptions &amp;
              issues log</span> and a reality-check against the programme and/or pay application.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <!-- Q4 -->
        <article class="group rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20 overflow-hidden">
          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">
            Collaboration
          </h2>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">
            Can you join calls with our GC, landlord, lender, or design team?
          </h3>
          <div class="mt-2 transition-all duration-200 ease-out max-h-0 opacity-0 group-hover:max-h-[2000px] group-hover:opacity-100">
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-700">
              Yes. In fact, it often makes the deliverables more valuable.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
              We can join review calls to walk stakeholders through the digital twin, highlight key
              risks and opportunities, and answer detailed questions about what was seen on site.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
              For clients on monthly bundles, a reasonable amount of review time is typically included.
              For ad-hoc work, we can add a small amount of <span class="font-medium">remote review time</span>
              to your quote or support ongoing calls on an hourly basis.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <!-- Q5 -->
        <article class="group rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20 overflow-hidden">
          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">
            Geography
          </h2>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">
            Do you work outside the United Kingdom?
          </h3>
          <div class="mt-2 transition-all duration-200 ease-out max-h-0 opacity-0 group-hover:max-h-[2000px] group-hover:opacity-100">
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-700">
              Our primary focus&mdash;and where our approach works best&mdash;is
              <span class="font-medium">across the United Kingdom</span>.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
              We can sometimes support work in other regions on a
              <span class="font-medium">case-by-case basis</span>. In those cases, travel is quoted separately.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <!-- Q6 -->
        <article class="group rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20 overflow-hidden">
          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">
            Branding &amp; neutrality
          </h2>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">
            Can you white-label under our brand?
          </h3>
          <div class="mt-2 transition-all duration-200 ease-out max-h-0 opacity-0 group-hover:max-h-[2000px] group-hover:opacity-100">
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-700">
              Yes, for many clients we act as a quiet, behind-the-scenes partner.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
              We can:
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-slate-700">
              <li>Use your logo and colour palette on reports.</li>
              <li>Present as part of your team in meetings and walkthroughs.</li>
              <li>Align deliverables to your internal templates and folder structure.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
              Regardless of branding, we remain <span class="font-medium">independent and vendor-neutral</span>:
              we don’t sell construction services and we don’t take fees from GCs or trades.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <!-- Q7 -->
        <article class="group rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20 overflow-hidden">
          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">
            Travel &amp; costs
          </h2>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">
            Is travel really included in your pricing?
          </h3>
          <div class="mt-2 transition-all duration-200 ease-out max-h-0 opacity-0 group-hover:max-h-[2000px] group-hover:opacity-100">
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-700">
              For typical U.K. sites, <span class="font-medium">travel and lodging are built into our published fees</span>.
              You see one number and don’t need to manage receipts or per diems.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
              Very remote locations or unusual routing may require separate travel quotation, which we’ll flag during quoting.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <!-- Q8 -->
        <article class="group rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20 overflow-hidden">
          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">
            On-site representation
          </h2>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">
            How does the Stakeholder Walkthrough &amp; Trade Day work in practice?
          </h3>
          <div class="mt-2 transition-all duration-200 ease-out max-h-0 opacity-0 group-hover:max-h-[2000px] group-hover:opacity-100">
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-700">
              Think of it as having a calm, technically literate representative on site to host your
              brokers, clients, landlords, and trades.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
              We run a structured walkthrough, help trades and stakeholders see the same scope,
              surface hidden risks, and sanity-check early budgets. Afterwards, you receive a concise
              note summarising attendees, key agreements, open questions, and major cost risks or
              opportunities.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
              This can be added to a standard visit or quoted as a standalone half- or full-day
              engagement.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <!-- Q9 -->
        <article class="group rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20 overflow-hidden">
          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">
            Practicalities
          </h2>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">
            What do you need from us before a visit?
          </h3>
          <div class="mt-2 transition-all duration-200 ease-out max-h-0 opacity-0 group-hover:max-h-[2000px] group-hover:opacity-100">
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-700">
              Ahead of each visit we’ll confirm:
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-slate-700">
              <li>Site address, approximate size, and basic building type.</li>
              <li>Primary decision you’re trying to make (renew, relocate, fund, phase, etc.).</li>
              <li>Any existing floor plans, test-fits, or landlord packs (if available).</li>
              <li>Access details, security requirements, and any site-specific PPE.</li>
              <li>Whether you’d like us to meet specific stakeholders or trades on site.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
              The clearer the brief, the more we can tailor the report and visuals to your team’s
              actual decision.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <!-- Q10 -->
        <article class="group rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20 overflow-hidden">
          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">
            Changes &amp; cancellations
          </h2>
          <h3 class="mt-2 text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">
            What happens if access changes or we need to reschedule?
          </h3>
          <div class="mt-2 transition-all duration-200 ease-out max-h-0 opacity-0 group-hover:max-h-[2000px] group-hover:opacity-100">
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-700">
              We understand that access windows, approvals, and tenant dates can move.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
              If you need to reschedule, we’ll always try to roll any pre-booked travel forward. If changes are made
              very late and incur non-refundable costs, we may need to <span class="font-medium">pass those through at face value</span>.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-500">
              We’ll be upfront about any potential charges and work with you to minimise them wherever possible.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
      <!-- CTA strip -->
      <div class="mt-12 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 px-6 py-8 sm:flex sm:items-center sm:justify-between">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">
            Still have questions?
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
            Share a bit about your portfolio, the decisions you’re facing, and the sites on your radar.
            We’ll tell you honestly whether Alturascope UK is the right fit and suggest a simple starting
            point.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-3 sm:mt-0 sm:justify-end">
          <a
            href="/uk/contact"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-slate-900 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-slate-800"
          >
            Talk to us
          </a>
          <a
            href="/uk/pricing"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-slate-300 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium text-slate-800 hover:bg-white"
          >
            View pricing
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>



